{"source_key":"sha256-903f1adf9377acdade8c215a48d8691f","record_index":156,"record_hash":"sha256:3b85d323941d9e02938d2baeeed803f557f3dcfe0f458d4fd224cb55beaaae05","timestamp":"2026-05-20T16:55:30.428Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: b02010\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 1498\nOutput:\n# Including Turns In Agentlog\n\nThis note explores an evolution of `but-agentlog`: add a durable concept of a\ncapture turn between the project-scoped session and the captured transcript\nrecords.\n\nThe motivation is the session-association problem. The older\n[Session Association Strategy](session-association-strategy.md) is right to be\ncautious about capture-time ownership, but it treats the captured session mostly\nas one coarse object. In practice, the hook flow already gives us a more useful\nunit: every stop hook invocation is effectively a capture after an agent turn.\n\nToday `but-agentlog` deduplicates transcript records into one project session:\n\n```text\nproject session -> transcript records\n```\n\nThat stores the conversation, but it loses which newly observed records belonged\nto which capture invocation. It also loses the repository state that was true at\nthat moment. A capture turn layer would preserve that missing context without\nforcing us to immediately claim that the session \"belongs\" to a branch, commit,\nchange, or pull request.\n\n## V1 Contract\n\nImplement v1 around persisted capture observations, derived indexes, and\nread-time association. Do not persist inferred ownership.\n\nPersisted hierarchy:\n\n```text\nproject\n  session\n    capture turns\n      transcript records\n```\n\nStorage shape:\n\n```text\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:turns = list<TurnSummary JSON>\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:turn:<turn-key> = TurnDetail JSON\n```\n\nCore rules:\n\n- A capture turn is created only when capture accepts at least one new\n  transcript record.\n- `TurnDetail.records` is an ordered array and is authoritative for rendering\n  order within the capture turn.\n- Backfilled capture turns may contain many logical conversation/provider turns,\n  so records must carry provider/display grouping metadata when available.\n- `turn_key` is `sha256-<32 lowercase hex chars>`, computed from UTF-8 stored\n  `session_key`, `s\n[TRUNCATED]\ns grouped by capture\n  turn or logical conversation/provider turn.\n- Review sharing starts from branch, review/PR, or change candidates and\n  verifies hits against `TurnDetail.observed_targets`. Scoring/ranking policy\n  belongs in the feature layer above these primitives.\n- Automatic association is private discovery. Anything exposed outside normal\n  repository-private scope must go through an explicit projection/redaction\n  step.\n- Results should be phrased as related-session evidence, not proof of authorship.\n\nV1 non-goals:\n\n- no durable inferred branch/PR/change ownership links\n- no path index\n- no commit index\n- no separate checked-out refs field\n- no graph `is_entrypoint` storage\n- no commit message summaries in capture turn snapshots\n- no index deletion/rebuild command\n\nThe rest of this document explains the rationale and implementation details\nbehind that contract.\n\n## Implementation Status\n\nAs of 2026-05-20, the `crates/but-agentlog` POC has moved from storage design\ninto the primitive read layer. The immediate goal is to merge coherent\nbuilding blocks, not the final review or handoff features.\n\nImplemented:\n\n- capture turns are persisted only when capture accepts new transcript records\n- transcript dedupe returns ordered accepted records for the capture invocation\n- `TurnSummary` and `TurnDetail` are stored in GitMeta\n- `TurnDetail.records` is ordered and authoritative for turn rendering\n- `turn_key` uses the specified truncated SHA-256 identity over session,\n  source, and ordered record hashes\n- transcript record hashes use the `sha256:<full lowercase hex digest>` shape\n- `previous_turn_key` links to the previous committed turn in the same session\n- session/source metadata, transcript records, record hashes, turn summary,\n  turn detail, and index memberships are written in one GitMeta `apply_edits`\n  batch\n- capture has a repo-local lock around the read/dedupe/write section\n- environment snapshots are captured best-effort and can be enriched later when\n  capture observes no new transcript records\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T16:55:30.428Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}